spec: concurrent_futures_extra278
version: ">=3.2"
backend: python_module(concurrent.futures._base)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/concurrent.futures.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/concurrent.futures.html — Python concurrent.futures module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-12"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/concurrent/futures/_base.py"
    - "concurrent_futures_extra99.zspec.zsdl — covers concurrent.futures module identity and submodule __name__ attributes"
  notes:
    - "This spec covers: concurrent.futures._base module identity (__name__, __spec__.name, __name__.__len__()); concurrent.futures._base.Error class identity (__name__, __module__, __qualname__, __bases__[0].__name__, __mro__.__len__()); concurrent.futures._base.BrokenExecutor class identity (__name__, __module__, __qualname__, __bases__[0].__name__, __mro__.__len__()); concurrent.futures._base.CancelledError class identity (__name__, __module__, __bases__[0].__name__, __mro__.__len__()); BrokenExecutor inherited method qualnames (__init__, __str__, __repr__ from BaseException). NEW in extra278: concurrent.futures._base.__name__=='concurrent.futures._base' (len=24); Error.__module__=='concurrent.futures._base'; Error.__bases__[0].__name__=='Exception'; Error.__mro__.__len__()==4; BrokenExecutor.__module__=='concurrent.futures._base'; BrokenExecutor.__bases__[0].__name__=='RuntimeError'; BrokenExecutor.__mro__.__len__()==5; CancelledError.__module__=='concurrent.futures._base'; CancelledError.__bases__[0].__name__=='Error'; CancelledError.__mro__.__len__()==5; BrokenExecutor.__init__.__qualname__=='BaseException.__init__' (inherited). All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-12."
    - "concurrent.futures._base.__name__.__len__() == 24 — 'concurrent.futures._base' is 24 characters: 'concurrent.futures.'=19+'_base'=5=24. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-12."
    - "concurrent.futures._base.Error.__mro__.__len__() == 4 — Error's MRO is [Error, Exception, BaseException, object] (length=4); Error is the base exception class for all concurrent.futures exceptions. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-12."
    - "concurrent.futures._base.BrokenExecutor.__mro__.__len__() == 5 — BrokenExecutor's MRO is [BrokenExecutor, RuntimeError, Exception, BaseException, object] (length=5); BrokenExecutor does NOT inherit from Error; it inherits from RuntimeError directly. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-12."
    - "concurrent.futures._base.CancelledError.__mro__.__len__() == 5 — CancelledError's MRO is [CancelledError, Error, Exception, BaseException, object] (length=5); CancelledError inherits from Error (not from BaseException directly), adding one level above Error's MRO. Note: this is concurrent.futures._base.CancelledError, distinct from the builtin asyncio.CancelledError. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-12."
    - "BrokenExecutor.__init__.__qualname__ == 'BaseException.__init__' — BrokenExecutor does not define its own __init__, so __init__.__qualname__ reports the inherited BaseException.__init__ qualname. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-12."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-12."
  created_at: "2026-04-12T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# concurrent.futures._base module identity — extra278
